.TH "z3fold_map" 9 "z3fold_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
z3fold_map \- maps the allocation associated with the given handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" z3fold_map
.BI "(struct z3fold_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "unsigned long handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool in which the allocation resides
.IP "handle" 12
handle associated with the allocation to be mapped
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Extracts the buddy number from handle and constructs the pointer to the
correct starting chunk within the page.
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the mapped allocation
